<block addressing="compact" define_as_param="true" display_name="slc_output_stage_regfile" external_ack="true" global="true" header_hermetic="true" intr_out_flopped="true" ipxact_exclude_param="true" name="slc_output_stage_regfile" refNameID="slc_output_stage_regfile" reset_type="async" rtl.strict_ports="true" rtl_pack_array="true" singleline_comment="true" sv_localparam="true"><reg name="os_data_gen" refNameID="os_data_gen"><field name="withhold_credit" offset="($OS_DAT_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>Maximum number of credits to withhold from release</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>withhold credits of os_data_gen fifo</doc></reg><reg name="os_credit_gen" refNameID="os_credit_gen"><field name="withhold_credit" offset="($OS_CDT_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>Maximum number of credits to withhold from release</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>withhold credits of os_credit_gen fifo</doc></reg><reg name="os_response_gen" refNameID="os_response_gen"><field name="withhold_credit" offset="($OS_RSP_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>Maximum number of credits to withhold from release</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>withhold credits of os_response_gen fifo</doc></reg><reg name="os_request_gen" refNameID="os_request_gen"><field name="withhold_credit" offset="($OS_REQ_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>Maximum number of credits to withhold from release</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>withhold credits of os_request_gen fifo</doc></reg><reg name="os_snoop_gen_bmp" refNameID="os_snoop_gen_bmp"><field name="withhold_credit" offset="($OS_BMP_SNP_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>Maximum number of credits to withhold from release</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>withhold credits of os_snoop_gen_bmp fifo</doc></reg><section display_name="gmesh_rqm_regfile" global="true" name="csr_slc_rqm" refNameID="gmesh_rqm_regfile" refparam.HAS_HR="1" refparam.HAS_NP="0" refparam.HAS_P0="1" refparam.HAS_P1="1" refparam.HAS_PW="0" refparam.HAS_SN="1" refparam.IS_MIC="0" refparam.IS_SLC="1" refparam.NUM_RATE_LIMITER_VECTORS="2" refparam.NUM_SAM_REGIONS="8"><section count="$NUM_SAM_REGIONS" name="rqm_sam_region_regfile" refNameID="rqm_sam_region_regfile"><reg name="cfg_rqm_region_start" refNameID="cfg_rqm_region_start"><field name="address" offset="27:0"><doc>SAM Region Start Address, 1MB granule (bits [47:20])
In the design, the 20 LSBs of the request address are asssumed to be 0x7FFFF.
SAM region is defined by cfg_sam_region_start[27:0] &lt;= chi_req.addr[47:20] &lt;= cfg_sam_region_end[27:0]</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_region_end" refNameID="cfg_rqm_region_end"><field name="address" offset="27:0"><doc>SAM Region End Address, 1MB granule (bits [47:20])
In the design, the 20 LSBs of the request address are asssumed to be 0x7FFFF.
SAM region is defined by cfg_sam_region_start[27:0] &lt;= chi_req.addr[47:20] &lt;= cfg_sam_region_end[27:0]</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_region" refNameID="cfg_rqm_region"><field encode="sam_memory_type_enum" ispresent="~ $IS_SLC" name="memory_type" offset="3:0"><doc><list name="sam_memory_type_enum" type="enum"><value doc="Memory Type Is Mi" name="MI">0</value><value doc="Memory Type Is Slc" name="SLC">1</value><value doc="Memory Type Is RMem" name="RMEM">2</value><value doc="Memory Type Is PConfig" name="PCONFIG">3</value><value doc="Memory Type Is PMem" name="PMEM">4</value><value doc="Memory Type Is Config" name="CONFIG">5</value><value doc="Memory Type Is Ccr0" name="CCR0">6</value><value doc="Memory Type Is Ccr1" name="CCR1">7</value><value doc="Memory Type Is Ccr2" name="CCR2">8</value></list>
            SAM Region Memory Type.
          </doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>MI</default></field><field name="numa_id" offset="5:4"><doc>The NUMA ID of a region</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="is_miphb" offset="8:8"><doc>The target is High Bandwidth MI-P</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="direct_eid" offset="((16 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 16"><doc>SAM Region Enumerate ID. Applicable only if target type is set to MI, RMem, PConfig or PMem.
Otherwise the target EID will be calculated by the hashing function or
configuration logic.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field ispresent="$IS_SLC" name="cxl" offset="28:28"><doc>The target is CXL.mem device (no need to hash over MI-Ds).
Relevant only in SLC System Address Mapping</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>SAM Region Valid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_PCIE_LUT" name="cfg_rqm_region_pcie" refNameID="cfg_rqm_region_pcie"><field name="id" offset="4:0"><doc>The target PCIe id.
To allow the reordering at the destination each PCIe
peer-to-peer request is assigned with PCIe ID.
For PCIe located in chiplet 0, pcie_id MSB shall be 0.
For PCIe located in chiplet 1, pcie_id MSB shall be 1</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><doc>The RQM SAM region configuration.
For the RQM to be functional, the SAM must be configured.
The SAM can be configured even during ACTIVE state, after config_done has been asserted.
To configure the SAM after config_done has been asserted, SW needs to:
1.Ensure there are no more transactions to this region.
2.Disable the region.
3.Config the region
4.Enable the region</doc></section><reg count="4" ispresent="($IS_SLC | $IS_MIF)" name="cfg_rqm_numa" refNameID="cfg_rqm_numa"><field encode="numa_size_enum" name="size" offset="1:0"><doc><list name="numa_size_enum" type="enum"><value doc="The NUMA ID represents F cluster" name="FULL">0</value><value doc="The NUMA ID represents H cluster" name="HALF">1</value><value doc="The NUMA ID is not used" name="NONE">2</value></list>
          The NUMA cluster size
        </doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>FULL</default></field><field encode="numa_location_enum" name="location" offset="5:4"><doc><list name="numa_location_enum" type="enum"><value doc="The SLC is part of this NUMA ID" name="LOCAL">0</value><value doc="The NUMA ID is at the same fabric as the SLC" name="PEER">1</value><value doc="The NUMA ID is at a remote fabric. SLC to SLC requests and snoops goes through MI-F" name="REMOTE">2</value></list>
          The location of the NUMA cluster with respect to the SLC
        </doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>LOCAL</default></field><doc>Numa cluster attributes, Relevant only in SLC System Address Mapping</doc></reg><reg count="4" ispresent="$IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_mid_index" refNameID="cfg_rqm_mid_index"><field name="to_eid" offset="($EID_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The MI-D hashing function outputs 2 bits index, this is the EID of
the MI-D that corresponds to the index.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_slc_hashing_override" refNameID="cfg_rqm_slc_hashing_override"><field name="en" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, the RQM will override the SLC Hashing EID
and will assign a new EID based on slc_hashing_override_value register</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="value" offset="((4 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 4"><doc>The value of the EID to use in case slc_hashing_override_en is set</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>the SLC hashing can be overridden by configuration.
The SAM of the source MI can be set to targets a single SLC</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_mid_hashing_override" refNameID="cfg_rqm_mid_hashing_override"><field name="en" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, the RQM will override the MI-D Hashing EID
and will assign a new EID based on mid_hashing_override_value register</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="value" offset="((4 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 4"><doc>The value of the EID to use in case mid_hashing_override_en is set</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>the MI-D hashing can be overridden by configuration.
The SAM of the source MI can be set to targets a single MI-D</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_NP" name="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_np" refNameID="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits"><field name="value" offset="($E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The E2E credits amount to load for EID = cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_eid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="eid" offset="((6 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 6" rtl.hw_wp="true"><doc>The EID that will be loaded with the cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_value.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>Set if the RQM can send flits to this EID on this VC.
e.g. If the RQM is in MI-C, en shall be 0 for all SLCs that are not
in the same NUMA cluster as this MI-C</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>End to End credit initialization register</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_P0" name="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_p0" refNameID="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits"><field name="value" offset="($E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The E2E credits amount to load for EID = cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_eid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="eid" offset="((6 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 6" rtl.hw_wp="true"><doc>The EID that will be loaded with the cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_value.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>Set if the RQM can send flits to this EID on this VC.
e.g. If the RQM is in MI-C, en shall be 0 for all SLCs that are not
in the same NUMA cluster as this MI-C</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>End to End credit initialization register</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_P1" name="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_p1" refNameID="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits"><field name="value" offset="($E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The E2E credits amount to load for EID = cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_eid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="eid" offset="((6 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 6" rtl.hw_wp="true"><doc>The EID that will be loaded with the cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_value.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>Set if the RQM can send flits to this EID on this VC.
e.g. If the RQM is in MI-C, en shall be 0 for all SLCs that are not
in the same NUMA cluster as this MI-C</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>End to End credit initialization register</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_PW" name="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_pw" refNameID="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits"><field name="value" offset="($E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The E2E credits amount to load for EID = cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_eid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="eid" offset="((6 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 6" rtl.hw_wp="true"><doc>The EID that will be loaded with the cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_value.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>Set if the RQM can send flits to this EID on this VC.
e.g. If the RQM is in MI-C, en shall be 0 for all SLCs that are not
in the same NUMA cluster as this MI-C</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>End to End credit initialization register</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_HR" name="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_hr" refNameID="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits"><field name="value" offset="($E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The E2E credits amount to load for EID = cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_eid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="eid" offset="((6 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 6" rtl.hw_wp="true"><doc>The EID that will be loaded with the cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_value.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>Set if the RQM can send flits to this EID on this VC.
e.g. If the RQM is in MI-C, en shall be 0 for all SLCs that are not
in the same NUMA cluster as this MI-C</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>End to End credit initialization register</doc></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_SN" name="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_sn" refNameID="cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits"><field name="value" offset="($E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The E2E credits amount to load for EID = cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_eid</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="eid" offset="((6 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 6" rtl.hw_wp="true"><doc>The EID that will be loaded with the cfg_rqm_initial_e2e_credits_value.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="en" offset="31:31"><doc>Set if the RQM can send flits to this EID on this VC.
e.g. If the RQM is in MI-C, en shall be 0 for all SLCs that are not
in the same NUMA cluster as this MI-C</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>End to End credit initialization register</doc></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_max_p0_p1" refNameID="cfg_rqm_max_p0_p1"><field name="total_credits" offset="$E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH : 0"><doc>Maximum credits that P0+P1 VC can consume together</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>10</default></field></reg><reg ispresent="~ $IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_cbusy_slc" refNameID="cfg_rqm_cbusy"><field name="max_out" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, CBusy is based on the maximum CBusy in the sliding window.
Otherwise CBusy is based on a factored average of the sliding window</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="window_size" offset="3:1"><doc>Set to value between 3 and 7.
WinSize sets the size of the sliding window to 2^WinSize entries.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>3</default></field><field name="busy_factor" offset="11:4"><doc>Average factor for the CBusy. BusyFactor is set in U1.7 fixed point.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>1</default></field><field name="aging_period" offset="31:12"><doc>Aging interval of the sliding window. If set to 0, the aging mechanism is disabled</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg ispresent="~ $IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_cbusy_mif" refNameID="cfg_rqm_cbusy"><field name="max_out" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, CBusy is based on the maximum CBusy in the sliding window.
Otherwise CBusy is based on a factored average of the sliding window</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="window_size" offset="3:1"><doc>Set to value between 3 and 7.
WinSize sets the size of the sliding window to 2^WinSize entries.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>3</default></field><field name="busy_factor" offset="11:4"><doc>Average factor for the CBusy. BusyFactor is set in U1.7 fixed point.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>1</default></field><field name="aging_period" offset="31:12"><doc>Aging interval of the sliding window. If set to 0, the aging mechanism is disabled</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg ispresent="~ $IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_cbusy_use_mif" refNameID="cfg_rqm_cbusy_use_mif"><field name="window" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, the RQM uses indications from the MI-F for CBusy calculation.
Should be disabled in MIs connected to a specific NUMA domain. (e.g. MI-C)</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg count="144" ispresent="$HAS_PCIE_LUT" name="cfg_rqm_pcie_peer_to_peer" refNameID="cfg_rqm_pcie_peer_to_peer"><field name="lut" offset="($EID_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>To allow the reordering at the destination each PCIe peer-to-peer request is assigned with PCIe ID
noting the source of the request and a sequence number for each request.
The target MI-F of each flits is set by this lookup table, the input of the table is
{SQN, TargetPCIe_id[3:0]} and the output is the EID of the target.
If the PCIe target is in a remote die, the LUT is used and the output of the
LUT is the EID of the target MI-F</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg count="8" ispresent="$HAS_MIF_HASH" name="cfg_rqm_target_mif_table_index" refNameID="cfg_rqm_target_mif_table_index"><field name="threshold" offset="5:0"><doc>The threshold that determines the TableIndex which is used as an
index to a lookup table of the target MI-F EID.
The table index is calulated as follows (A = {SLC[0],SLC[6:2]}) :
if A&lt;TH0: TableIndex = 0
elif A&lt;TH1: TableIndex =1
elif A&lt;TH2: TableIndex = 2
elif A&lt;TH3: TableIndex = 3
elif A&lt;TH4: TableIndex = 4
elif A&lt;TH5: TableIndex = 5
elif A&lt;TH6: TableIndex = 6
elif A&lt;TH7: TableIndex = 7
else: TableIndex = 8
The thresholds TH0-TH7 shall be set according to the following table and the number of
active MI-Fs:
TH Idx   Eight Active MI-Fs      Nine Active MI-Fs
0                 7                    6
1                 14                   12
2                 21                   19
3                 28                   25
4                 39                   35
5                 46                   41
6                 53                   48
7                 60                   54</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><exceptions><exception index="0" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd7</default></exception></exception><exception index="1" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd14</default></exception></exception><exception index="2" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd21</default></exception></exception><exception index="3" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd28</default></exception></exception><exception index="4" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd39</default></exception></exception><exception index="5" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd46</default></exception></exception><exception index="6" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd53</default></exception></exception><exception index="7" type="reg"><exception name="threshold" type="field"><default>6'd60</default></exception></exception></exceptions></reg><reg count="9" ispresent="$HAS_MIF_HASH" name="cfg_rqm_table_index_to_mif" refNameID="cfg_rqm_table_index_to_mif"><field name="eid" offset="($EID_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>A lookup table of the target MI-F EID, the index to the lookup table
is the table index calculated based on cfg_rqm_target_mif_table_index_threshold.
The lookup table should be configured with the active MI-F EID in order from left
to right. The EID of the leftmost active MI-F should be written to the first entry
of the table (MI-F0 EID). If there are 9 active MI-Fs then the EID of the
rightmost active MI-F is written to the last entry (MI-F8 EID) and if there are 8
active MI-F the EID of the rightmost active MI-F is written to the MI-F7 EID entry.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg ispresent="$HAS_MIF_HASH" name="cfg_rqm_mif_hashing" refNameID="cfg_rqm_mif_hashing"><field name="en" offset="0:0"><doc>If enabled, target EID of PCIe remote memory access is calculated by MI-F hashing.
If not enabled, the EID is taken from the Direct EID of the SAM region</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>1</default></field></reg><reg ispresent="~ $IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_cbusy_drop_prefetch_tgt" refNameID="cfg_rqm_cbusy_drop_prefetch_tgt"><field name="en" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, the RQM drops PrefetchTgt requests if the CBusy value is
equal to or greater than cfg_rqm_cbusy_drop_prefetch_tgt.value</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="value" offset="5:4"><doc>The CBusy threshold, if the CBusy value is equal to or greater than this threshold
and cfg_rqm_cbusy_drop_prefetch_tgt_en, The RQM drops PrefetchTgt requests</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>The RQM can optionally drop PrefetchTgt requests according to the CBusy state.
The RQM holds a configurable CBusy threshold and if this option is enabled by
software PrefetchTgt requests are dropped by the RQM if the CBusy value is
equal to or greater than the CBusy threshold</doc></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_src_numa_id_override" refNameID="cfg_rqm_src_numa_id_override"><field name="en" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, the RQM will override the src_numa_id and will assign
the src_numa_id field based on cfg_rqm_src_numa_id_override.value register</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="value" offset="5:4"><doc>The value of the src_numa_id to use in case
cfg_rqm_src_numa_id_override.en is set</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><doc>Option to override the request src_numa_id</doc></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_eid" refNameID="cfg_rqm_eid"><field name="default_mia" offset="($EID_WIDTH - 1) : 0"><doc>The enumerate ID of the Default MI-A that serves as the completer for unmapped transactions</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field name="dvm_hub" offset="((16 + $EID_WIDTH) - 1) : 16"><doc>The enumerate ID of the DVM hub</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg count="7" name="cfg_rqm_arb_wrr" refNameID="cfg_rqm_arb_wrr"><field name="weight" offset="7:0"><doc>Weight of each VC in the VC weighted round robin arbiter.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>255</default></field></reg><section count="$NUM_RATE_LIMITER_VECTORS" name="cfg_rate_limiter_regfile" refNameID="cfg_rate_limiter_regfile"><reg count="4" name="cfg_rqm_rate_limiter" refNameID="cfg_rqm_rate_limiter"><field name="vector" offset="31:0"><doc>Rate limiter bit map.
the limiter runs over these bits in a cycle,
enabling a request only when a bit is set (e.g. if we want a 50% rate limiter,
we will set only the even bits).
The bitmap[reg_index][bitmap_j] corresponds to 32 * reg_index + bitmap_j</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>4294967295</default></field></reg><doc>For SLC :
We have 2 vectors, cfg_rate_limiter_regfile[0] is used when throttling_bit = 0,
cfg_rate_limiter_regfile[1] is used when throttling_bit = 1.
For Non SLC :
We have 12 vectors, and the vector we use is based on the CBusy and the req color.
Vectors mapping :
4'd0 - CBusy 00, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd1 - CBusy 00, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd2 - CBusy 00, Red Rate limiter vector.
4'd3 - CBusy 01, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd4 - CBusy 01, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd5 - CBusy 01, Red Rate limiter vector.
4'd6 - CBusy 10, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd7 - CBusy 10, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd8 - CBusy 10, Red Rate limiter vector.
4'd9 - CBusy 11, Green Rate limiter vector.
4'd10 - CBusy 11, Yellow Rate limiter vector.
4'd11 - CBusy 11, Red Rate limiter vector.</doc></section><reg count="4" ispresent="$IS_MIC" name="cfg_rqm_core_p1_opcodes" refNameID="cfg_rqm_core_p1_opcodes"><field name="bitmap" offset="31:0"><doc>If a bit is set, a core request to SLC is transmitted with P1 VC.
The MSB of the opcode is not used by
the core so we need only NUM_REQ_OPCODES/2 (128) bits.
By default the opcodes that are p1 are :
ReadShared
ReadClean
ReadOnce
ReadNoSnp
ReadUnique
ReadNoSnpSep
ReadOnceCleanInvalid
ReadOnceMakeInvalid
ReadNotSharedDirty
CleanUnique
MakeUnique
MakeReadUnique
