If a bit is set, request to High Bandwidth MI-P will be directed to
EID = direct_eid (as configured in the relevant sam region).
If a bit is 0, request to High Bandwidth MI-P will be directed
to EID = (direct_eid + 1)
The bitmap[reg_index][bitmap_j] corresponds to 32 * reg_index + bitmap_j</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><exceptions><exception index="0" type="reg"><exception name="bitmap" type="field"><default>32'd16</default></exception></exception><exception index="1" type="reg"><exception name="bitmap" type="field"><default>0</default></exception></exception><exception index="2" type="reg"><exception name="bitmap" type="field"><default>0</default></exception></exception><exception index="3" type="reg"><exception name="bitmap" type="field"><default>0</default></exception></exception></exceptions></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_color_override" refNameID="cfg_rqm_color_override"><field name="en" offset="0:0"><doc>If set, the RQM will override the input flit's color
and will assign a new color based on override_color_value register</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field><field encode="color_enum" name="value" offset="5:4"><doc><list name="color_enum" type="enum"><value doc="Green Color" name="GREEN">0</value><value doc="Yellow Color" name="YELLOW">1</value><value doc="Red Color" name="RED">2</value></list>
          The value of the color to use in case override_color_en is set
