Shall match the SAM configurtion - base address for config region</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg count="3" ispresent="~ $IS_SLC" name="cfg_rqm_ccr" refNameID="cfg_rqm_ccr"><field name="base_address" offset="27:0"><doc>The CCR is set with base EID pointing to the EID of the first agent in the CCR and is incremented with the
address offset. 1MB granule (bits [47:20]).
Base address of a CCR region must be aligned with the size of the CCR region.
Shall match the SAM configurtion - start address for the corresponding CCR region.
CCR0 supports up to 128 agents of 1MiB each. CCR0 address range is 128MiB.
CCR1 supports up to 16 agents of 1MiB each. CCR1 address range is 16MiB.
CCR2 supports up to 32 agents of 16MiB each. CCR2 address range is 512MiB.</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_core_config_space" refNameID="cfg_rqm_core_config_space"><field name="base_address" offset="27:0"><doc>The base address of the core config space. 1MB granule (bits [47:20])
Shall be aligned to 128MiB.
Shall match the SAM configurtion - base address for CCR region</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><reg name="cfg_rqm_chiplet" refNameID="cfg_rqm_chiplet"><field encode="numa_domain_enum" name="is_half_numa" offset="0:0"><doc><list name="numa_domain_enum" type="enum"><value doc="The RQM is in a chiplet that has a single NUMA domain. (F cluster)" name="FULL_CLUSTER">0</value><value doc="The RQM is in a chiplet that has two NUMA domains. (H cluster)" name="HALF_CLUSTER">1</value></list>
          The Numa domain topology of the chiplet the RQM reside in
        </doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>FULL_CLUSTER</default></field><field encode="chiplet_rotation_enum" name="is_rotated" offset="4:4"><doc><list name="chiplet_rotation_enum" type="enum"><value doc="The RQM is not in a rotated die" name="NOT_ROTATED">0</value><value doc="The RQM is in a rotated die" name="ROTATED">1</value></list>
          The indication regarding the die rotation
        </doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>NOT_ROTATED</default></field><field ispresent="$HAS_PCIE_LUT" name="id" offset="8:8"><doc>The chiplet ID the RQM reside in. chiplet 0 contains
Numas 0 &amp; 1 (if exist) and chiplet 1 contains Numas 2 &amp; 3 (if exist)</doc><sw>rw</sw><hw>ro</hw><default>0</default></field></reg><doc>RQM CSR Register File</doc></section><doc><list type="param"><value localparam="true" name="OS_DAT_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH" private="1">4</value><value localparam="true" name="OS_CDT_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH" private="1">4</value><value localparam="true" name="OS_RSP_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH" private="1">4</value><value localparam="true" name="OS_REQ_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH" private="1">4</value><value localparam="true" name="OS_BMP_SNP_FIFO_DEPTH_WIDTH" private="1">4</value><value localparam="true" name="NUM_SAM_REGIONS" private="1">8</value><value localparam="true" name="EID_WIDTH" private="1">10</value><value localparam="true" name="NUM_RATE_LIMITER_VECTORS" private="1">2</value><value localparam="true" name="E2E_CREDIT_WIDTH" private="1">6</value><value localparam="true" name="IS_SLC" private="1">1</value><value localparam="true" name="IS_MIC" private="1">0</value><value localparam="true" name="IS_MIF" private="1">0</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_NP" private="1">0</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_P0" private="1">1</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_P1" private="1">1</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_PW" private="1">0</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_HR" private="1">1</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_SN" private="1">1</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_PCIE_LUT" private="1">0</value><value localparam="true" name="HAS_MIF_HASH" private="1">0</value></list>
        SLC Output Stage CSR Register File
